        <div class="row">

             <div class="col-md-3">
                <p class="lead">Ingredients</p>
                 <ul class="list-group">
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">1/2 cup</span>
                    Banana chips
                  </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">1/2 cup</span>
                    Rolled oats
                  </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">1 tpsn</span>
                    Cocoa powder
                  </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">1/4 cup</span>
                    Chunky peanut butter
                  </li>
                   <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">3 tpsn</span>
                    Honey
                  </li>                                                                        
                </ul>

                <p class="lead">Additional Images</p>
                <%= image_tag "chips.jpg", :class => 'img-responsive image-spacing'%>
                <%= image_tag "rolledoats.jpg", :class => 'img-responsive image-spacing'%>
                <%= image_tag "honey.jpg", :class => 'img-responsive image-spacing'%>                
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-9">

                <div class="thumbnail">
                    <%= image_tag "bites.jpg", :class => 'img-responsive'%>
                    <div class="caption-full">
                        <h3 class = "header-spacing">No-Bake Banana Bites</h3>
                    </div>

                        <p class = "p-spacing">These frozen delights are fun and delicious. The bite-sizes are perfect to go with your favorite TV shows. </p>

              </div>
              <div class = "thumbnail">
                    <div class="caption-full">
                        <h3>Preparation Instructions
                        </h3>
                        <em>Total Time: 20 minutes</em>
                    </div>

              <ol class = "preparation-instructions">
                  <li>
                   Crush the banana chips with the back of a butter knife (or roughly chop in food processor) and add to a large mixing bowl. Add the oats and cocoa to the banana chips and mix together. Stir in the peanut butter and honey.
                  </li>
                  <li>lace in the refrigerator and chill for 30 minutes. Once chilled, remove from the refrigerator and form 1-inch balls with your hands.</li>
                  <li>Place onto a parchment-lined baking sheet and chill for 15-30 minutes (until firm). Store in a sealed container in the refrigerator for up to one week.</li>
                
                </ol>

